                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.047,
                                "byte_start": 104620,
                                "byte_stop": 140878,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has the opinion in case 06-571, Watson versus United States, which he asked me to announce."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 9.047,
                                "stop": 14.972,
                                "byte_start": 140878,
                                "byte_stop": 164597,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.972,
                                "stop": 30.801,
                                "byte_start": 164597,
                                "byte_stop": 227918,
                                "text": "Petitioner, Michael A. Watson traded narcotics for a pistol and was indicted for using a pistol during and in relation to a drug trafficking crime in violation of 18 U.S.C. Section 924(c)(1)(A)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.801,
                                "stop": 44.271,
                                "byte_start": 227918,
                                "byte_stop": 281730,
                                "text": "He pleaded guilty, but reserved the right to appeal on the ground that receiving a firearm in exchange for narcotics is not use of a firearm within the meaning of Section 924 (c)(1)(A)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.271,
                                "stop": 47.308,
                                "byte_start": 281730,
                                "byte_stop": 293956,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals rejected this argument."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.308,
                                "stop": 56.455,
                                "byte_start": 293956,
                                "byte_stop": 330527,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk of the Court, we hold that Watson\u0027s conduct does not constitute use of a firearm, we reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.455,
                                "stop": 59.824,
                                "byte_start": 330527,
                                "byte_stop": 344006,
                                "text": "We have construed the same provision twice before."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.824,
                                "stop": 66.762,
                                "byte_start": 344006,
                                "byte_stop": 371696,
                                "text": "Both times, we relied primarily on the ordinary or natural meaning of the verb \u0022in context\u0022."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.762,
                                "stop": 79.579,
                                "byte_start": 371696,
                                "byte_stop": 423000,
                                "text": "This appeal to ordinary English leaves the Government without much of a case for -- for in regular speech, we would not say that Watson used a firearm by merely receiving it in a barter transaction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.579,
                                "stop": 84.305,
                                "byte_start": 423000,
                                "byte_stop": 441913,
                                "text": "The Government\u0027s two main arguments for trumping ordinary English are unavailing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.305,
                                "stop": 95.194,
                                "byte_start": 441913,
                                "byte_stop": 485485,
                                "text": "First, the Government argues that under a neighboring provision, Section 924(d)(1), the verb used is employed in a manner that includes receipt in barter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.194,
                                "stop": 112.932,
                                "byte_start": 485485,
                                "byte_stop": 556434,
                                "text": "It asks us to import this meaning into Section (c)(1)(A), but this argument over reads our precedence and forgets that in the two different subsections, the common verb speaks to different issues in different voices and at different levels of specificity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.932,
                                "stop": 129.606,
                                "byte_start": 556434,
                                "byte_stop": 623098,
                                "text": "Second, the Government warns that a decision in favor of Watson would create unacceptable asymmetry with Smith versus United States, a prior case in which we held that trading of firearm for narcotics does constitute use of the firearm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.606,
                                "stop": 146.894,
                                "byte_start": 623098,
                                "byte_stop": 692271,
                                "text": "Whatever the tension between the -- that result in the outcome here, law depends on respect for language and would be served better by statutory amendment if Congress sees asymmetry, then by racking statutory language to cover a policy it fails to fit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.894,
                                "stop": 150.021,
                                "byte_start": 692271,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
